Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the connectivity behavior of the boot2podman_machine system:

```plantuml
@startuml boot2podman_machine

actor User
participant "CLI" as CLI
participant "Libmachine" as LM
participant "Driver" as D
participant "Provisioner" as P
participant "Host" as H
participant "SSH" as SSH
participant "Podman VM" as VM

User -> CLI: Execute command
activate CLI

CLI -> LM: Create/Manage VM
activate LM

LM -> D: Load driver
activate D

D -> LM: Return driver instance

LM -> H: Create host
activate H

H -> D: Initialize VM
D --> H: VM initialized

H -> P: Provision VM
activate P

P -> SSH: Connect to VM
activate SSH

SSH -> VM: Execute provisioning commands
activate VM

VM --> SSH: Command results
deactivate VM

SSH --> P: Provisioning complete
deactivate SSH

P --> H: VM provisioned
deactivate P

H --> LM: Host ready
deactivate H

LM -> CLI: VM management complete
deactivate LM

CLI -> User: Display result
deactivate CLI

@enduml
```